Biology :
Oxysarcodexia varia
is more abundant during the spring and summer in
Argentina
and southern Brazil (
Ferreira 1979
;
Mariluis et al. 2007
;
Mulieri et al. 2008
). Moreover, this species showed preference for faeces bait, and is regarded as asynanthropic because of its higher abundance in rural areas (
Ferreira 1979
;
Mariluis et al. 2007
;
Mulieri et al. 2008
). In previous works,
O. varia
was reared on dung (
Mendes & Linhares 2002
) or dead insects (
Blanchard 1939
). Flower visitor of Apiaceae (
Eryngium horridum
), Asteraceae (
Baccharis juncea
,
Helianthus annuus
), Euphorbiaceae (
Sebastiana brasiliensis
), Rhamnaceae (
Colletia paradoxa
,
Discaria americana
,
Scutia buxifolia
).
